(188, 1, '2025-10-18 07:41:01', '2025-10-18 07:41:01', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\r\n<div>\r\n<div>  United Kirat Rai Organization of America (UKROA) is a non-profit organization established in 2007 with the aim to practice, preserve, and promote Kirat Rai culture in the United States of America.</div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>     Our goal is to preserve our ethnic Kirat history, Kirat religion (Munthum), scripts, traditions, culture and languages while maintaining cultural and ethnic harmony. We will preserve and continue our Kirat Rai culture for next generation.</div>\r\n<div>       </div>\r\n<div>UKROA  practices the principles of non violence, mutual respect, coexistence, kindness, cooperation and respect for human rights. We firmly believe in social harmony, interdependence and respect. We condemn any form of violence, social injustice, and violation of human rights.</div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n</div>\r\nUnited Kirat Rai Organization of America (UKROA) is a non-profit organization established in 2007 with the aim to practice, preserve, and promote Kirat Rai culture in the United States of America.</div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>     Our goal is to preserve our ethnic Kirat history, Kirat religion (Munthum), scripts, traditions, culture and languages while maintaining cultural and ethnic harmony. We will preserve and continue our Kirat Rai culture for next generation.</div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n<div>       UKROA  practices the principles of non violence, mutual respect, coexistence, kindness, cooperation and respect for human rights. We firmly believe in social harmony, interdependence and respect. We condemn any form of violence, social injustice, and violation of human rights.</div>\r\n<div> </div>\r\n</div>\r\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'About Us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-10-18 07:41:01', '2025-10-18 07:41:01', '', 2, 'http://localhost/ukroa/?p=188', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
